text: Kemal Meredow (born 2 February 1994) is a Turkmen male ju-jitsu practitioner. He represented Turkmenistan at the 2018 Asian Games and claimed a bronze medal in the men's ne-waza 56kg event. == References == Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Turkmenistan male martial artists Category:Ju- jitsu practitioners at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Medalists at the 2018 Asian Games Category:Asian Games bronze medalists for Turkmenistan Category:Asian Games medalists in ju-jitsu
